options.option_text: The first term measures bias shift; the second term measures covariancemismatch.
Both terms are dominated by the generator’s variance.
The first term measures variance difference; the second measures mean shift.

question_texts: FID compares real and generated image distributions by assuming they follow multivariate Gaussian distributions in a feature space extracted from a pretrained neural network. Which layer’s activations are typically used to compute this feature space in practice?

options.option_text: The output logits of the generator
The first convolution layer of the discriminator

questions.question_text_1: Which of the following are valid reasons why GAN training based on JSD minimization is unstable?
question_texts: Which of the following are valid reasons why GAN training based on JSD minimization is unstable?

options.option_text: JSD saturates when the supports of pdata and pg do not overlap.
Gradients for the generator can vanish when the discriminator becomes toostrong.
JSD is not continuous w.r.t. the parameters of the generator distribution.
JSD always provides unbiased gradients in high dimensions.
